    and 
    $$(\sigma\triangle \sigma) \circ \Delta(\xi_I)=(\sigma\triangle \sigma)(\xi_I,\xi_I)=\sum_{A,B\subseteq I}(\xi_A,\xi_B).$$
    The two summations agree: in the first summation $J$ is fully determined by $A$ and $B$ and can be ignored.
